## High Finding

### 6. `Clone_ProducesEqualObject` (line 28–34) — Missing independence assertion

The test verifies that `Clone()` copies values, but never checks that the clone is **independent** of the original. If `Clone` returned `this`, the test would still pass. Always mutate one side and verify the other is unaffected.

```csharp
// AFTER — add independence check
var clone = original.Clone();
Assert.AreEqual(original.Timeout, clone.Timeout);
Assert.AreEqual(original.Retries, clone.Retries);

// Verify independence — mutating clone must not affect original
clone.Timeout = 999;
Assert.AreEqual(30, original.Timeout); // still 30
```

